<!--- ===American Sign Language ===
In [[American Sign Language]] (ASL), the topic of the sentence, that is the focus of the sentence, is put at the beginning. For example, in translating the English phrase "We are going to the store tomorrow", some possible ASL sentences, literally translated, could be: *"WE GO STORE TOMORROW." *"TOMORROW, STORE WE GO." (Topicalization, TOMORROW is the focus) *"*STORE, WE GO TOMORROW." (Topicalization, STORE is the focus)
Proper ASL structure, though, uses the time indicator first, so the proper ASL form would be the second one: "TOMORROW, STORE WE GO." --->
